.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-http_bench \- Lightweight HTTP benchmark: N requests, configurable concurrency, reports p50/p95/p99,
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility http_bench
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Lightweight HTTP benchmark: N requests, configurable concurrency, reports p50/p95/p99,
.SH BACKENDS (TRIED IN ORDER)
.PP
.IP \(em 4
\fBhey\fP — Go-based, best statistics (pip install hey or download binary)
.IP \(em 4
\fBwrk\fP — C-based, high performance (apt install wrk)
.IP \(em 4
\fBcurl\fP — built-in, always available
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bench https://example.com
bench https://api.example.com -n 200 -c 10
bench https://httpbin.org/post -m POST -d '{"key":"value"}' -H 'Content-Type: application/json'
bench https://example.com -n 1000 -c 50 --json
.EE
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Flag   |   Meaning   |   Default
\fC-n, --requests N\fP   |   Total requests   |   50
\fC-c, --concurrency N\fP   |   Parallel workers   |   5
\fC-m, --method M\fP   |   HTTP method   |   GET
\fC-H, --header H\fP   |   Custom header (repeatable)   |   —
\fC-d, --data DATA\fP   |   Request body   |   —
\fC--timeout SEC\fP   |   Per-request timeout   |   10
\fC--keep-alive\fP   |   HTTP keep-alive   |   off
\fC--json\fP   |   Machine-readable output   |   off
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success (even if errors)
\fC1\fP   |   All requests failed
\fC2\fP   |   Argument / dependency error
